# SDKWork Drive edge rate limiting (example)

Use this pattern in front of multi-replica Drive HTTP services. In-process
rate limiters in `sdkwork-router-drive-*` are a defense-in-depth layer only;
edge limits must be enforced at the gateway for production HA deployments.

## Nginx (`limit_req`)

```nginx
# deployments/nginx/drive-edge-rate-limit.conf.example
limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=drive_open_api:10m rate=30r/s;
limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=drive_app_api:10m rate=120r/s;

server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name drive.example.com;

    location /open/v3/api/drive/share_links/ {
        limit_req zone=drive_open_api burst=60 nodelay;
        proxy_pass http://sdkwork-drive-open-api:18082;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    }

    location /app/v3/api/drive/ {
        limit_req zone=drive_app_api burst=240 nodelay;
        proxy_pass http://sdkwork-drive-app-api:18080;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    }
}
```

## Kubernetes Ingress (nginx ingress controller)

```yaml
metadata:
  annotations:
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: "120"
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier: "2"
```

Tune limits per tenant SLA and pair with WAF rules for abusive share-link traffic.
